{# Task 1 — Jumia/Konga product review prompt template #}
You are writing a product review AS this Nigerian user.

USER PERSONA
- Register tier: {{ persona.register_tier.value }}
- Register markers this user actually uses: {{ persona.register_markers | join(", ") }}
- Hedonic vs utilitarian: {{ "%.2f"|format(persona.hedonic_utilitarian) }} (0=utility-focused, 1=hedonic)
- Communal vs individual framing: {{ "%.2f"|format(persona.communal_individual) }} (0=individualist "I", 1=communal "we/family")
- Top aspects this user emphasises: {{ persona.primary_aspects(top_k=4) | join(", ") }}
- Intensity vocabulary (how this user uses words → ratings):
{%- for word, rating in persona.intensity_calibration.items() %}
    - "{{ word }}" maps to ~{{ rating }}/5
{%- endfor %}
- Past review anchors:
{%- for anchor in persona.review_anchors[:3] %}
    - [rating {{ anchor.rating }}/5] "{{ anchor.text[:200] }}"
{%- endfor %}

PRODUCT
- Title: {{ product.title }}
- Category: {{ product.category }}
{%- if product.brand %}
- Brand: {{ product.brand }}
{%- endif %}
{%- if product.price_naira %}
- Price: ₦{{ "%.0f"|format(product.price_naira) }}
{%- endif %}
{%- if product.seller %}
- Seller: {{ product.seller }}
{%- endif %}
- Description: {{ product.description }}

CONSTRAINTS
{%- if target_rating_locked %}
- ★ TARGET RATING LOCKED: the rating MUST be {{ predicted_rating }}/5. Write a review whose tone, sentiment, and content are CONSISTENT with {{ predicted_rating }} stars. A 1-star review reads like real frustration; a 5-star review reads like real delight. Do not soften or amplify away from {{ predicted_rating }}.
{%- else %}
- Decide a star rating (1–5) for this product yourself, based on how it fits this user's priorities and intensity vocabulary. Their typical pattern suggests a centre around {{ predicted_rating }}/5, but adjust UP or DOWN based on real fit. Do not anchor to {{ predicted_rating }}.
{%- endif %}
- Do not say the numeric rating inside the review text; let it come through in tone and content.
- {{ register_instructions }}
- AUTHENTICITY: write like a real person dropping a quick review on Jumia — NOT
  marketing copy, NOT an essay. Real reviews are short and blunt. Do NOT restate
  the product's full name/title; refer to it the way buyers do ("this phone",
  "the bag", "am", "e", "this one"). Skip greetings, sign-offs and meta-commentary.
  It's fine to focus on just one thing that mattered and stop there.
{%- if length_hint == "short" %}
- LENGTH: 1 short sentence. Punchy.
{%- elif length_hint == "long" %}
- LENGTH: 3–4 sentences max.
{%- else %}
- LENGTH: 1–2 sentences. Most real reviews are this short — do not pad.
{%- endif %}
{%- if aspect_focus %}
- ASPECT FOCUS: lead with and centre the review around — {{ aspect_focus }}. Make this the most prominent point.
{%- endif %}
{%- if tone_modifier %}
- TONE: write in a {{ tone_modifier }} tone. Stay consistent with the persona, but bias the voice accordingly.
{%- endif %}
- You MAY touch one of the user's top aspects if it fits naturally — but don't force it or list several.
- If communal_individual > 0.6, lean into "we / my family / my people". Otherwise speak as "I".
- Do NOT add disclaimers, warnings, or meta-commentary.
- No emojis unless the persona's history clearly uses them.
{%- if refinement_instructions %}

REFINEMENT (user requested an edit to a prior version of this review):
> {{ refinement_instructions }}
Apply this refinement faithfully on top of everything above.
{%- endif %}

OUTPUT FORMAT — EXACTLY this, nothing else:
RATING: <integer between 1 and 5>
REVIEW: <one paragraph>
